    "Harvey Cox, Henry M. Morris": "Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` Kotsensis\nMitzvot Torah, pr. Affirm, 76, Bartenora in Misn. Maccot, c. 2. sect.\n5. Ft116 --  T. Bab. Yoma, fol. 9.\n5. Ft123 --  Zohar in Leviticus fol. 26.\n5. Ft158 --  Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]`. Antiqu. 50:4. c. 4. sect.\n5. Ft167 --  Bereshit Rabba, sect. 21. fol. 19. 1. & Mattanot Cehunah in ib.\n[v_Gen_3_24] Aben Ezra in Gen 3:\n5. Third round of Discourses (chapters 22-31). Eliphaz speaks even more briefly; Job answers; then Bildad speaks briefly. Zophar remains silent. Job, still insisting he is innocent of known sin, follows with an extensive, summarizing statement.\n5. Third round of Discourses (chapters 22-31). Eliphaz\nspeaks even more briefly; Job answers; then Bildad speaks\nbriefly. Zophar remains silent. Job, still insisting he is\ninnocent of known sin, follows with an extensive,\nsummarizing statement.",
